xii) —(CR102aR102b)aN(R101)2; for example, —NH2, —CH2NH2, —NHCH3, —CH2NHCH3, —N(CH3)2, and —CH2N(CH3)2;
xiii) halogen; —F, —Cl, —Br, and —I;
xiv) —(CR102aR102b)aCN;
xv) —(CR102aR102b)aNO2;
xvi) —(CHj′Xk′)aCHjXk; wherein X is halogen, the index j is an integer from 0 to 2, j+k=3; the index j′ is an integer from 0 to 2, j′+k′=2; for example, —CH2F, —CHF2, —CH2CH2F, —CH2CHF2, —CF3, —CCl3, or —CBr3;
xvii) —(CR102aR102b)aSR101; —SH, —CH2SH, —SCH3, —CH2SCH3, —SC6H5, and —CH2SC6H5;
xviii) —(CR102aR102b)aSO2R101; for example, —SO2H, —CH2SO2H, —SO2CH3, —CH2SO2CH3, —SO2C6H5, and —CH2SO2C6H5; and
