Step D relates to the reaction of the 5-aryl or 5-heteroaryl-3-hydroxy-2-carboxypyridine formed in step C with a compound having formula D1, wherein X is chosen from —OH, —OR3, —NR4R5 or —OM1 as defined herein above, to form one of the following:
i) a prolyl hydroxylase inhibitor;
ii) a prolyl hydroxylase inhibitor prodrug;
iii) an admixture of prolyl hydroxylase inhibitors;
iv) an admixture of prolyl hydroxylase inhibitor prodrugs; or
v) suitable pharmaceutical salts thereof.
